e swear words in the English sense.  The thing is that none of them are really as powerful as the other kind of insult.  The best/simplest way to insult someone would be to use teme or kisama (offensive versions of the word &quot;you&quot;), and -te yagaru (which adds a really hateful nuance).  For example: <br><br>&quot;What are you doing?&quot; /  &quot;What's up?&quot;<br>Ima nani shiteiru no?<br>&quot;Hey a$$hole, what the f*ck are you doing!?&quot;<br>Oi kisama, nani shite yagateiru no ka?<br> <br>But like you can see, there is no work for f*ck in the Japanese sentence, and a$$hole was just a rough form of &quot;you&quot;.  Depending on context, someone might not even put those into the English translation.  This stuff is complicated, unfortunately you can just step right in and start doing it, at least not well.<br><br> <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#aaaaaa><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub25.ezboard.com/bpolykarbonbbs.showLocalUserPublicProfile?login=razorscooter09>razor scooter09</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Pre-Karbonite</span><br> <font color=#336699>(1/22/02 12:38:19 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub25.ezboard.com/fpolykarbonbbsfrm5.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=611.topic&index=3>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re:  i want to learn japanese.</span><hr size=1> i want to learn swear word or insults to swear at my teachers or some other people so they dont know what im saying<br> <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#CCCCCC><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub25.ezboard.com/unoahrei.showPublicProfile?language=EN>NoahRei</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://www.artistnation.com/members/paris/noahrei/1942-1947r.jpg" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Karbonite</span><br> <font color=#336699>(1/22/02 3:48:00 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub25.ezboard.com/fpolyka